Class AXmlAttribute<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.jimple.infoflow.android.axml.AXmlElement
      • soot.jimple.infoflow.android.axml.AXmlAttribute<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - determines the attribute's type. Currently Integer, Boolean and String are supported.

    public class AXmlAttribute<T>
extends AXmlElement
    Represents an attribute of an Android XML node.
    Author:
    Stefan Haas, Mario Schlipf, Steven Arzt

      • getType

        public int getType()
        Returns an integer which identifies this attribute's type. Currently if AXmlAttribute is typed as Integer this will return NodeVisitor.TYPE_INT_HEX, typed Boolean will result in NodeVisitor.TYPE_INT_BOOLEAN and otherwise (even if not typed as String) this returns NodeVisitor.TYPE_STRING.
        Returns:
        integer representing the attribute's type
        See Also:
        NodeVisitor.TYPE_INT_HEX, NodeVisitor.TYPE_INT_BOOLEAN, NodeVisitor.TYPE_STRING

      • getAttributeType

        public int getAttributeType()
        Returns an integer which identifies this attribute's type. This is the type originally passed to the constructor.
        Returns:
        integer representing the attribute's type
        See Also:
        NodeVisitor.TYPE_INT_HEX, NodeVisitor.TYPE_INT_BOOLEAN, NodeVisitor.TYPE_STRING
